A British soldier was killed overnight by a bomb  explosion near an army roadblock in Keady village in southern Ulster, near the  border with the Irish Republic, police said Sunday.
The soldier died shortly after being taken to hospital. Another soldier  was slightly wounded in the attack, which has not yet been claimed.
In another incident in west Belfast, a mixed patrol of British troops and  police fired several plastic bullets at a group of youths throwing stones and  bottles at them.
Four soldiers were slightly hurt. Police did not report any civilian  casualties.
